        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 1 at 4:48PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles east of Speaks to
Boling-Iago. Movement was east at around 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Campo, Wharton, and Pierce.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
